caption: Decadent desserts satisfying the sweet tooth without overdoing it. Fun inviting atmosphere on the third level of the 808 building.
I love Fruit Roll cake and Fruit tea.

Love cakeM! I love the store because their cakes are all made from the scratch. I've tried strawberry short cake, mont blanc cake (OMG! So GOOD! I believe they only serve on Wednesday and Thursday), chocolate cake, fruit tart, lemon tart... and they were all amazing! They serve local grown coffee and tea (Lilikoi tea). I will definitely go back again!!!

I love this Japanese-French style cake shop💛 I didn’t eat cakes in US it’s because most cakes are too sweet. However CakeM’s cakes a not overly sweet, and everything’s are home made😍 I ordered my Wedding cakes and desert bar here and all my guests loved them🎂🍰🍴 With their quality of cakes, the price is actually low🤙I highly recommend this shop to everyone!

Tried this place 3 times.  The second time, walked over there only to find a printout taped to the door saying they were closed that day (during hours that they are otherwise open).  What they offer costs way too much for what you're getting, especially considering that the items look better than they taste.  More style than substance.

Small and beautiful Japanese style (French style?) cakes. Shop is pretty too. Not too sweet like American especially like Hawaiian sweets. Very polite  Japanese-English bilingual stuff members. Everything is very Japanesey. I would go back again! (Cakes in my photo look squished only because of my driving. They looked perfect when I got them)
(Translated by Google) Pretty and delicious cake shop Yul-Hyun-Tan-Ju-Tzu-Jun-Chan-Chan-Chan-Chan-T-C _-_-  (Original) 이쁘고 맛있는 케이크집 율일한 딴쩜은 쭈인이 읿뽄쌀람ㅠㅠ
They can accept your order custom cake at least $32 and it takes for two weeks with custom fee $20. Ordering at the last minutes less than two weeks costs more $20.

First off, this review is a mixture of the in house desserts and the custom cupcakes I had ordered. My dad had their cream puffs and loved it. Said it was the best he had so far in Hawaii. I also had their strawberry shortcake and thought it was ok (had better).  Now on to the custom cupcakes! The design of the cupcakes were ADORABLE. Just what we had asked for. However, upon the first bite I was left confused. I clearly remembered ordering cupcakes, not corn bread. It wasn't even good corn bread. Super dry. The butter cream frosting tasted like room temp butter mixed with sugar. (I love frosting btw so not biased!)  All in all, a huge disappointment because if I wanted corn bread, I would just go Zippys and not pay $5 per. I think their custom cakes are probably ok (based on the strawberry shortcake).. but I would give the cupcakes a hard pass. Do try the cream puffs though.  (The 2 stars is for the cream puffs and design of the cupcakes.)

(Translated by Google) I don't eat chocolate cake by myself first, but I got it as a souvenir. It was really delicious. Fruit tarts, cheese tarts, etc. are all delicious.  (Original) チョコケーキは自分ではまず選ばす食べませんが、お土産でいただきました。本当〜に美味しかったです❣️フルーツタルト、チーズタルト等々どれも美味しいです。

A very delightful simple atmosphere.  Cute little pastry shop with Japanese pastry style and taste very light on sweetness.  I highly recommend it.  Japanese and English speaking staff. We ordered a birthday cake and it was amazing.  And Honestly, you have to try  the cream puffs, the best I have had in Hawaii.
